    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES62-5A, ES62-5D, ES67-5A AND
        ES67-5D - DISASSEMBLY - SHIFT TOWER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Standard Shift Tower</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301002">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301002" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301002" filename="../figg13/G1301002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Standard Shift Tower</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HANDLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPRING RETAINER LOCK PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ROCK SHAFT PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. GASKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. LEVER HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. SNAP RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. LEVER COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. SPRING RETAINER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts and lockwashers. Separate the lever housing from the shifter
                    housing and gasket. Lift it straight up.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the shift lever housing on edge in a vise.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press the spring retainer against the spring. Remove the lock pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the lever cover up the shift lever and remove the rock shaft snap ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tap the rock shaft free of the lever housing and remove the shift lever. Remove and
                    discard the gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift lever handle. Slide the lever cover, spring retainer, and spring off
                    the lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash all parts thoroughly and inspect the lever and rock shaft cross holes for excessive
                    wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check spring tension by comparing the old spring to a new one. Replace if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Gimbal Shift Tower</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301003">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301003" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301003" filename="../figg13/G1301003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Gimbal Shift Tower</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CABLE STRAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. YOKE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TRUNNION SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SHIFT TOWER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. PIVOT PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. SHIFT LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. BOOT</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. SHIFT KNOB</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Begin disassembly by cutting the two tie cables which secure the boot.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift knob bezel, retaining nut, washers, and shift knob. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s13010_22.xml" xrefid="f1301072">Figure 72</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the boot off the shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two trunnion screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the lever from the tower.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the shift yoke from the lever, simply press out the pivot pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash all parts. Inspect them thoroughly for damage. Replace parts as necessary.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
